From: Jiri Bohac <jbohac@suse.cz>
Subject: kABI fix for alarmtimer_restart functionality
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI fix
References: bsc#1214298

patches.fixes/alarmtimers-change-alarmtimer-functions-to-return-al.patch modifies
the prototype of the alarm callback function.
struct alarm is embedded struct k_itimer, so the change propagates to kABI.
However, the callback should only ever be manipulated by the non-exported alarm_init() 
function, setting the callback to either alarmtimer_nsleep_wakeup or alarm_handle_timer.

Thus it is safe to fake old prototype for kABI.


--- a/include/linux/alarmtimer.h
+++ b/include/linux/alarmtimer.h
@@ -31,7 +31,11 @@ enum alarmtimer_restart {
 struct alarm {
 	struct timerqueue_node	node;
 	ktime_t			period;
+#ifdef __GENKSYMS__
+	void			(*function)(struct alarm *);
+#else
 	enum alarmtimer_restart	(*function)(struct alarm *, ktime_t now);
+#endif
 	enum alarmtimer_type	type;
 	bool			enabled;
 	void			*data;
